   \'93He got mad because he wanted to get mad. I don\'92t think I was impertinent until that last question, and he deserved that.\'94\par
   Bellows didn\'92t answer.\par
   \'93Anyway I really didn\'92t want to make him angry ... well, maybe I did in a way.\'94 Susan thought for a few moments. \'93You see, I talked with this patient only an hour or so ago. He was the patient I had to leave the ICU for. It\'92s just so unbelievable; he was a functioning, normal human being. And ... I ... we had a conversation and I felt like I knew something about him. I even took a liking to him in a way. That\'92s what makes me mad or sad or both. And Harris, his attitude made it worse.\'94\par
